    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="319"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2629</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1916, noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received April 25, 8 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3800. There is a quiet conflict on between Military and Navy on one side and many
                    sincere Germans on the other side who advocate a decent conduct of submarine
                    war. Last number of Maximilian Harden’s magazine entitled <hi rend="italic">If I
                        Were <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi> has just been confiscated <pb facs="0528" n="242" xml:id="pg_242"/> by
                    military authorities. It had been on sale some days and in it Harden claimed
                    that the President was right and had only made proper claims against
                    Germany.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
